The paper deals with coding theory and graph theory, which are both relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The Grassmann graph and projective-space graph are both combinatorial structures, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (discrete mathematics). The paper also discusses encoding and decoding algorithms, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.CC). The mention of network coding suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). Finally, the paper discusses computational complexity, which is relevant to computer science theory and algorithms (cs.SI).
